Method Detail

marshal

public String marshal(T value,
                      String marshalledValue)
Description copied from interface: Marshaller
Marshals data from value into marshalledValue, or possibly a new B instance. Only non-null property values from value are used to update marshalledValue. This implies that if marshalledValue is not null, a "merge" operation is performed, pushing non-null data from value into marshalledValue, but otherwise leaving any existing data in marshalledValue alone.

Specified by:
marshal in interface Marshaller<T,String>
Returns:
marshalledValue (or a new B instance) containing data from value .
